snippet.title: Massive pro-Houthi rally held in Yemeni capital
snippet.description:
Tens of thousands of Yemenis take to the streets of Sanaa in a massive show of support for the Houthi-led bloc that retains control of the capital and several major towns and cities across the country, in one of the biggest demonstrations in Yemen since 2011 protests that forced President Ali Abdullah Saleh to step down. Rough Cut (no reporter narration).

snippet.title: Items from Ali's career hit the auction block
